        </ol>
        
        <p>We will send you a confirmation mail with all information as soon as 
            we receive your order. When we receive the payment, we will send 
            you a second mail that includes PDF documents with your eTickets.</p>
        
        <h2>Personalised items</h2>

        <p>Personalised items are items that are assigned to a specific person. Many items <strong>must</strong> be personalised, for example each week or day ticket must belong to a specific juggler. For some other items, you can <strong>choose</strong> to personalise them, so they will be handed out to the right person. For example, if you order additional gala-show tickets, you can assign each one to a specific person to avoid confusion later ("Is this mine or yours?").</p>

        <h2>Persons in your order</h2>

        <p>To make it easy for you to keep track of the persons in your order, we have added the "My Persons" button in the menu. It takes you to an overview of all persons for which you have entered any information. Here you can view and edit their details, e.g. correct a name that you have accidentally misspelled. </p>

        <h2>Late payments, cancellation of orders, transfering of tickets</h2>

        <p>If we don't receive your payment within 14 days after your order, 
            we will have to cancel your order. Sorry. To avoid that, best pay 
            immediately!<br>
            If you have already paid your order and received your e-ticket, but 
            for some reasons cannot attend EJC 2015, the best thing to do is 
            find another juggler who can take over your ticket. When you have 
            done that, it is very important that you let us know who the ticket 
            shall be transferred! Please contact  
            <a href="mailto:prereg@eja.net">prereg@eja.net</a> in this case. If 
            there is no-one to take over your order, you can find the guidelines 
            for refunds in our 
            <a href="<?php echo $this->url('info', array('action' => 'terms')); ?>">ERS terms and agreement document</a>.</p>
